						<div class="bio-img">
							<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/josephjellis-e1760796235926-150x150.jpeg" width="96" height="96" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/josephjellis-e1760796235926.jpeg 2x" alt="Joseph J. Ellis" class="avatar avatar-96 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-96 alignnone photo" />						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Joseph J. Ellis</h4>
												<p>Joseph J. Ellis is the author of many works of American history, including <em>Founding Brothers: The Revolutionary Generation</em>, which was awarded the Pulitzer Prize, and <em>American Sphinx: The Character of Thomas Jefferson</em>, which won the National Book Award. He lives on Hawk Mountain, in Plymouth County, with his wife and two labradoodles.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			
